## Part 4: Maximum Achievable Potential

### With Current Dependencies (No Changes)

| Capability | Current Level | Achievable Max | How |
|-----------|:------------:|:--------------:|-----|
| **Digital PDF Speed** | 3-10s per doc | **0.5-2s** per doc | Eliminate triple-write, direct BytesIO |
| **Scanned PDF Speed** | 45-120s per doc | **15-35s** per doc | Async threads, smart DPI, parallel pages |
| **Multi-file Speed** | Sequential (N × time) | **~N/3 × time** | `asyncio.gather()` with 3 workers |
| **Indian Bank Name Detection** | ~0% | **~92-95%** | Add 15+ Indian bank patterns |
| **Account Number Extraction** | ~0% (Indian) | **~70-85%** | Expanded regex, fuzzy matching |
| **Digital PDF Column Mapping** | ~80% (US) / ~50% (Indian) | **~92-95%** | Dynamic gap threshold, better table_settings |
| **Scanned PDF Column Mapping** | ~70% | **~88-93%** | X-coordinate clustering via numpy |
| **Date Parsing** | ~90% | **~97%** | Already good; minor edge cases |
| **Debit/Credit Classification** | ~85% | **~93-95%** | Better column alignment feeds better classification |
| **Overall Extraction Accuracy** | ~65-75% | **~88-95%** | Cumulative effect of all improvements |

### What Cannot Be Achieved Without New Dependencies

| Limitation | Why | What Would Fix It |
|-----------|-----|-------------------|
| GPU-accelerated OCR | PaddleOCR runs on CPU only (paddlepaddle CPU build) | `paddlepaddle-gpu` + CUDA |
| Layout-aware document understanding | PaddleOCR treats each text box independently | LayoutLMv3, Docling, or PaddleOCR PP-Structure table mode |
| Handwritten text recognition | PaddleOCR `lang="en"` is print-text focused | Specialized handwriting models |
| Multi-language statements | Only English patterns supported | Multi-lang PaddleOCR models + Hindi/regional regex |
| Sub-5-second scanned PDF processing | CPU-bound PaddleOCR inference | GPU acceleration or lighter models |

### Theoretical Speed Floor (Hardware-Limited)

On a standard dev machine (4-core CPU, no GPU):
- **Digital PDF:** ~0.3-0.5s per page (pdfplumber is fast)
- **Scanned PDF:** ~2-3s per page (PaddleOCR CPU minimum)
- **10-page scanned statement:** ~20-30s minimum (CPU-bound)
- **With GPU (RTX 3060+):** ~0.3-0.5s per page → 10-page statement in ~3-5s

